( Bot Hunter Analysis Report) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 1. Classifiers) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The application implements two classifiers. The first is a rules-based classifier that) Tj
T*
(scores repeated query/domain pairs, repeated queries, high-volume domains, dense) Tj
T*
(region/browser/OS clusters, exact time-to-click reuse, same-second bursts, and) Tj
T*
(implausibly fast clicks. The second is an unsupervised k-means anomaly model over) Tj
T*
(standardized behavioral features. Events far from their closest centroid receive higher) Tj
T*
(anomaly scores.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 2. Anomalies found) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The run analyzed 149,239 events and flagged 3,781 events as bots \(2.53%\). The strongest) Tj
T*
(explainable patterns were:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- repeated query: 3,583 events) Tj
T*
(- very short query: 2,089 events) Tj
T*
(- repeated query/domain pair: 2,015 events) Tj
T*
(- same-second click burst: 1,952 events) Tj
T*
(- heavy region/browser/os cluster: 1,889 events) Tj
T*
(- high-volume clicked domain: 1,661 events) Tj
T*
(- extreme time-to-click: 167 events) Tj
T*
(- implausibly fast click: 27 events) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The dashboard exposes these same signals with sample events so a business user can) Tj
T*
(inspect the likely automated behavior without reading model internals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 3. Filtering options) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practical filters for similar datasets include dropping or quarantining traffic from) Tj
T*
(repeated query/domain pairs, repeated exact ttc values, dense same-second bursts, and) Tj
T*
(events above the combined anomaly threshold. For ad-billing workflows, the safest) Tj
T*
(starting point is to quarantine high-confidence bot traffic for review, then move to) Tj
T*
(automatic suppression once performance is validated against labeled outcomes or) Tj
T*
(chargeback evidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 4. Rationale and generalization) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The heuristic model is transparent and easy to convert into policy. The k-means model) Tj
T*
(catches multivariate oddities that a small rule set may miss. Both should generalize) Tj
T*
(when bot traffic is repetitive or mechanically timed, but they may miss human-like bots) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
